        "description": "<p><em>Mille Bornes</em> is a computer implementation of the card game of the same name. Players can play cards to travel a certain distance. The deck also contains hazard cards which can be used to block another player and remedy cards that are used to fix these situations. Lastly Safety cards can be used to immediately block a hazard and granting an additional turn. A round ends when a player reaches 700 points and the game ends when a player reaches 5000 points. Points are earned from distance traveled, but additional bonus points can be gained from playing safeties or getting to 700 points without the use of the highest value distance card. The game is played against the computer.</p>",
